,Not Recommended,441870,21967760,"Posted: 21 March, 2016",all,Snort Cannon,"Oh OutDrive where did it all go wrong ?I wanted to like this game I really did, but man it's not worth it, so let's get into it.In OutDrive you play as the Driver. His girlfriend is shot and you hook her up to your Delorean and you have to maintain a certain speed to keep her alive.Drive too slow she dies, drive too fast she dies.The neon visuals and overall the entire design is fantastic, but sadly that's where the good ends and the bad begins.The game is endless and there's no ending what so ever, and to experience everything the map has takes you at least 15 minutes and after that there's nothing else. There are obstacles in the road like road blocks and ramps. There are also random encounters like traffic and a helicopter which shoots at you, but it does absolutely nothing and after a few shots the helicopter explodes.The entire game gets tiring after a few minutes and after that there's nothing to do.The soundtrack is great and is really fun to drive around to listen to the music, but it's not worth to play the game just to listen to the music.I wanted to like this game, I really did, but I can't, my honest recommendation is to wait until Powerdrive 2000 comes out this coming May,Final Rating:3/10 - Don't BotherIf you liked this review please consider giving this game a thumbs up and if you disliked post in the comments on what you disliked.For more reviews follow Snort's Review curator pagehere- follow for regular updates on reviews for other games!"
