76561198007738668,Not Recommended,441870,21411828,"Posted: 23 February, 2016",all,Black Seven,"DO NOT PURCHASE THIS IF YOU INTEND TO USE AN XBOX-360 CONTROLLER.IT IS SIMPLY UNPLAYABLE.If you configure the BOOST function (secondary) to your Controller button, your car will boost forward, but the girl will die. If you use the keyboard it works fine, since it does both, boost and save the girl.If you are trying to put the Acceleration function to the controller trigger, you wont be able to do it on the first Accel option you see, scroll down, and you will see another Accel option, that one will let you do it. The dev, put separate ones for the controller. EXCEPT for BRAKE. There is no way to put Brake on the the other trigger. It will however accept a button on the secondary for the only Brake function on the Control configuration launcher area. BUT NO AXIS FOR BRAKING.X-Box 360 controller needs to be configured before you play. EVERY TIME YOU PLAY.There are no options in-game whatsoever. You have graphics and control settings on the launcher.Graphics Options on the launcher do not save for me. Ever. You need to change it every time you play. SERIOUSLY, EVERY TIME!No Audio Options. NONE.Game does not tell you how to play, as simple as it is, you should at least know what you should do or not do, I kept getting game over after a few seconds even though the car was already quite fast, it was only when I tried to use the keyboard left shift button that I noticed that the key function was bugged on the controller function.I don't mind unfinished games, I rarely finish most of my games anyway, what I do not like under any circumstance are non-functional games. That's what this is for me. I simply can not play it, regardless of how cheap it is, it should at least work.I was looking forward to playing this, and simply writing a review that says ""This is what you would get if Kung Fury, TopGear and Distance had a Baby!"". The soundtrack alone is fantastic. The concept is really cool too. Hopefully they will add more functionality to the game, some in-game menus (not very hard to do), and just make it playable. Looking forward to when I can delete everything that's written above and just keep that catchy sentence, until then, hold on to your money."
