,Not Recommended,441870,28659899,"Posted: 25 December, 2016",all,Game On 95,"Before I purchased the game I seen all of these negative reviews and wondered why. The Gameplay looks pretty good, the music is amazing, and the graphics are pretty nice to look at. When I purchased the game and played it for a little... I soon found out why. Now don't get me wrong, the game is pretty cool and fun to play, however there are absolutely no options for the game. no raising or lowering the sound, no changing controls, not even any other game mode options. All you do is pretty much drive. Your goal is to get a high score which I feel shouldn't be it main focus, especially if you're trying to keep a girl alive! Speaking about her, I feel like she's not even there, sure the meter tells us how she’s doing but other than that we get no dialogue from her or the driver, we don't even get to see what they look like in game. Now I've seen some people encounter a lot of glitches, however I didn't have this problem to an extreme. My game glitched out only once and it was for crashing into an oncoming car. I also feel a like there is a lack of action, only a little bit though. There are cars that come after you and a Helicopter that guns you down, but those are in very small sections, after you pass the sections they're gone. Then it's a dead, lonely, empty road. At least have a few cop cars chase for a bit in those sections, really make it like I'm the game, that there is a purpose, to make me feel hype.  I feel like this game should have some kind of story behind it, I mean how you like a movie where the person just drives to keep this girl alive, no ending. At least stay focused on the story and makes the high score part a secondary game mode. Do I recommend the game? No, not unless there do some serious updating, if you're interested buy it on sale."
