,Not Recommended,441870,21545194,"Posted: 29 February, 2016",all,HijackedBrain,"Great looking graphics, good soundings ""new retro wave"" ish music, 80s electro.BUTkeyboard only controls, for a driving game .... it's killing it. But somehow when you get the control everything will be fine.Maybe too fine... Once you mastered the controls, the game become extremely easy. Road is empty, you'll have to face an helicopter shooting at you maybe every 5 minutes.And about the track, 50% of the time you just driving on an empty road, with no traffic and empty surroundings. It gets boring pretty quickly, and I'm pretty sure the map is not generated. During my 20 playtime, I came across the same city, with the same crossroads at least 10 times.About the gameplay, the game expect you to drive not too slow to keep your ""girlfriend"" alive but also NOT TOO FAST.... DO NOT GO TOO FAST ! in a driving game ?!?! Excuse me ? So you've got to juggle with your tubo, toggling it off and on every 10 seconds. Which make the camera pan, zoom in, zoom out, every time... It gets really nauseous.Is this game a sequel to outrun ?Not at all, the crossroad are there but feel empty. I don't feel like accomplishing something when I survive past a crossroad. The background does not change, there is not a map at the end of the run showing off my progress, just a plain timer. Everyhing I'm doing feels empty, and serve no purpose.So in conclusion, in its current game, OutDrive could be the core of a good driving game. But it really needs more polish on the controls, the gameplay, the backgrounds, and need more gamemode.I really wish the dev will update this game, so I can change my review to a positive one.PS : Also beware the game being made on Unity Personal Edition, it is not really well optimized. I barely hit 30 FPS (specs :Intel Core i7-4700MQ + GeForce GT 740M + 12 GB DDR3)PPS : After some research, it looks like dev are just trying to cash in and do a clone of PowerDrive 2000 .... Gonna do some more research but will probably ask for a refund if it turns out to be true.PPS : Quote from developers""It is not a game.Only music concept.Mimimum mechanics - maximum music""So yeah, probably won't be fixed/updated. Refund on its way"
