,Recommended,441870,32736426,Posted: 24 June,all,Declirious,"To truly get the experience of the game we need to take it wayyyy back the the groovy 80’sA simpler time, full of dank music, dank colors, and the best (most cheesy) action moviesOutdrive is currently only 50 cents, you could either buy a condom or this, so what do you get for that little money?The game starts with a very retro cinematic, it shows you that yo grill gets shot, and to keep her alive you connect her to the speedometer of you car. You have to maintain speed to keep her alive.Go to slow, and her heart's stops, go to fast and her heart overloads.The game is a endless runner, but unlike most you have full control over your character (in the style of a racing game), most games would have you move between columns. Not here, here you have full controll.The controls are simple, W for gas, S for reverse, Space for Drift, and Shift for turbo. One thing I really like about this is that you can use turbo for however long you want, there is no limit. But while using turbo the car is harder to turn. It adds a nice level of depth to a otherwise brainless game.Every once and awhile you will come across giant helicopters that try to kill you. This is nice because without it the game is kinda easy.But it might be a good thing, this is not a game that needs a lot of strategy. It’s the kind of game that makes you melt into your chair and forget about all of your problems.One reason for that is it’s amazing soundtrack, it’s very retro and basey, using synths and other “Vaperwave” sounds. Something also amazing about it is that it’s all made by individual creators that have these songs in real albums. Buy the soundtrack on steam, it’s pretty fantastic.One cool thing about the game is that the tempo of the music is directly tied to your speed, so the faster you go the more tense the song gets.Moving through the amazing landscapes while listening to the music will leave you in a almost trance like stateThis game is also really visually pleasing, It’s a eyegasm that will leave your spectacles sticky.It’s using a very retro wave graphical style, it’s like a mix of gta vice city and tron.So if you have a little bit of leftover money sitting in your steam wallet, you should give this a try. You won’t be disappointed."
