,Not Recommended,441870,28784316,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,UltraMan✫,"I see why this product has mixed reviews.The game itself is meh.The graphics are great and all the animations are very true to the 80's era.The soundtrack itself was worth playing for an hour or so as well since I'm heavily into the 80's retro synth genre.Unfortunately if your car so much as slows down too much or bumps into a wall or obstacle, this wonderful music gets interrupted with a very VHS style sound glitch(this is intentional as a design element, mind you).This wouldn't be that bad if you could maybe turn it off but you can't. At first it's kinda funny because it reminds you of when VHS tapes(if you're old enough to remember them) would lose tracking and make the audio slur for a moment. The novelty of this wears of very quickly when wanting to just listen to the music, though.The controls are somewhat slippery and while they're not that hard to pick up, there seems to be no real option for recovery whenever you make a hard crash. There's no way to reverse the car and once you've crashed into something like a wall of cars in front of you it makes you pretty much S.O.L. Your only option is to just restart the level.It's priced normally at $3 but isn't even worth that much.The best thing I walked away with was the new set of tunes I'll be jamming to in the near future. Ironically enough I feel like this was the REAL purpose of this game. Not to make a decent little quickie you could pick up but more so to expose these retro synth artists(none of which I've even heard of until now funny enough) and get music sales going.How am I so sure? It's a part of the main menu, lol.You want a good 80' style racing game? Sorry. It ain't here.Hopefully that will be Power Drive 2000(the game this one clearly ripped off).You want some good 80's style retro synth tunes? Here you go.These are all the links they provided in the game to buy the music from each artist. These are at least worth it if you're into the genre like I am and definitely worth the money more than this game.https://future80s.bandcamp.com/album/around-every-corner-digital-deluxehttps://soundcloud.com/logic-puzzlehttps://nammusic2.bandcamp.com/releaseshttps://3force.bandcamp.com/releaseshttps://d-noise.bandcamp.com/releaseshttps://soundcloud.com/quasarshttps://wingsofsolace.bandcamp.com/https://spaceinvaderspaceinvader.bandcamp.com/https://retouch.bandcamp.com/https://priusansich.bandcamp.com/You're welcome."
