,Not Recommended,441870,29258321,Posted: 14 January,all,HypnoticSheep,"PROS+The visuals are amazing, and perfectly 80s. I kept slowing down just to watch a section of terrain roll past, and the opening cinematic had a great 80s-noire feel to it. I half expected the car to ask me if I was a bad enough dude to save the girlfriend.+The music is phenomenal, though I wish you could control it at all.CONS-There is literally nothing to do in this game but drive. The only obstacles are turns and jumps, and because of how terrible the controls and handling are these obstacles will usually end the game.-The car handles like a brick on crisco. While holding forward it shimmies left and right for no reason, even on straightaways. While drifting (the only other control in the game) the tires' friction spikes and drops randomly, meaning you need to mash left and right to avoid slamming into a wall.- Touching a wall at all is like running headfirst into a tree. There's no grinding around a curve, you just get slammed to a stop and, usually, turned around. At one point my car flipped on its side, and the game decided that was my new road. I was only able to drive straight up into the air until the meter dropped and the game ended.- There's no validation on the randomly-generated road. A jump can spawn that fires you directly into the wall, at which point you get to choose whether you hit the barricade and lose or take the jump and lose.SUMMARYThe game is, unfortunately, not fun. It looks and sounds awesome, but the gameplay designer seriously dropped the ball here. I understand it wasn't meant to be a game, just an ""aesthetic concept"", but the bugs and shoddy controls ruin the experience completely.PS: After 8minthere's a couple more obstacles: a helicopter and a city street. The heli shoots at you (which does nothing) and fires rockets that spin you around and throw chunks of debris onto the street. Neither is too bad, but if a chunk of debris lands on you while you're spun out you can't turn around in time to avoid losing. Heli spawns every 8min. City street materializes cars in front of you that act like walls.Still not really worth the time."
