 the menu, just a bit, but the ""dev"" went to ""Photoshop"" and downloaded a font and put it in the cover of the game...This game had a ""TON"" of potential to be put, it`s sad that it doesn`t even have complete ""stages"", they`re just a segment  of every stage you can be respawned at, now, it would make it more fun if it had achivments, like ""Rift for 10 seconds"" or ""Use your turbo for 1 minute""...but it seems like a uncompleted game...-The designs makes it, i will only recommend this game to the only ones who likes ""Retro Aesthetics"", over all, Good job on the game, and if this game was the first game ever made by the ""dev"", then congratulations, you are 3 steps more further than anybody else who is starting to design games-This game absolutely deserves a 6/10, not more  nor less, ""6/10""(P.S: This should have the entire soundtrack of the movie ""Drive"", it will match amazingly well)"
