,Not Recommended,441870,32707824,Posted: 23 June,all,Airdrajoker,"I wanted to like this game. It looks great, sounds great...and then you get to where you're actually trying to play it and the whole thing falls apart. I get it, you're selling more of an experience rather than a game, but it's a frustrating one.Any adjustments to screen resolution, graphics quality, or key mapping must be done outside of the game itself in a launcher. I'm playing with a controller, and changing the button mapping in particular results in a significant delay. The in-game menus are also incredibly laggy.When you get into the game itself, you're monitoring engine temperature vs speed to the point that you just might be distracted from the rest of the controls just not being able to handle some of the sudden very tight turns you're expected to make. It's not fun, and it's more annoying than anything else. (Seriously, the line of cars at the ramp, which I think was designed to add some level of challenge to this, was just annoying instead of an actual challenge--with these controls, getting past it is more a matter of luck over skill.)There's potential here, but it's hidden underneath irritating controls and laggy menus."
