,Not Recommended,441870,33457841,Posted: 11 July,all,Scholl,"The objective of the game without the cheesy ""save the girl"" plot: You have to maintain a certain speed driving on a windy road with occasional road blocks for as long as possible - going too fast or too slow for too long and it's game over.The game looks nice and has awesome music - the two things that lead me to buy it. I got it at a generously discounted price and I'm not complaining, but I would not buy it for it's 3 EUR price tag - and here's why:- I get it that this is ""not a game, but an aesthetic concept"" (a detail that I have to admit paid absolutely no attention to when I bought it), but it has an objective - drive as long a possible - and it would've been a good game if it had rewards at certain milestones or some more variation, changing scenery, or even as little as a scoreboard to compete against.- The physics is a little weird. Sometimes you won't lose your speed to a head-on collision with the invisible wall at the two sides of the road, sometimes barely scraping the wall stops you completely.- To make it worse, the game sometimes does not register correctly that you're driving too fast or too slow. Sometimes coming to a full stop registers as adequate speed, with no apparent logic behind it.- You can get stuck on invisible obstacles around road blocks and inside walls in the tunnels.- The helicopter shows up and proceeds to shoot you through the mountainside when in a tunnel.- The road is flickering inside tunnels.- While the game runs smooth, the menu is slow as all hell, also the loading screen locks up for half a minute before starting the game.- I just found out that the menu is not scaled down when you run at a lower resolution. There are some menu items that are simply just not visible when running at 720p, which is bad design.I understand what the developers were going for, but 3 EUR is too much for this. Also, if it is an aesthetic concept please just let me enjoy the music and watch the scenery and not make me rage over the handling and the glitches. Or make it into a proper game."
