76561198099013322,Recommended,441870,33801770,Posted: 25 July,all,Penguin Shuttle,"I'm a sucker for 80's retro stuff, so of course I'm biased, but I like this game. It's a good time killer for playing in short bursts. Sometimes I just like to do a mindless task for a little bit while thinking about other stuff, and this game fills that desire. I see some other people compaining about the controls, but they don't seem bad to me. It's just a standard WASD/Shift/Space control scheme. The car itslf doesn't control like a real car, but this isn't a simulator. For a game where all you do is veer left or right and occasionally drift, the controls are fine for me. What matters to me most is that the game is relaxing and the soundtrack is great.I only have one compaint: the graphics revert back to the lowest settings every time you open the game. However, since you always see the settings menu before the game starts, and since there are really only 3 settings to change (resolution, AA, windowed/fullscreen), it literally only takes like 5 seconds to change them back to where you want them. It's not too tedious for me, but it would be nice if it were fixed in an update. I got this on sale for under a dollar so it's hard to nitpick at it, but even at full price... it's only $3. You'll know within the first 15-30 minutes whether or not you like it, and there's always the refund system if you don't. This game definitely isn't for everyone, but if 80's retro / synthwave is your niche, my adivce is to at least give it a try."
