,Recommended,441870,34432219,Posted: 23 August,all,Jedzenie,"Mixed feelings on this one. I paid 55 cents for this game, which is why I didn't bother refunding. I would if it cost the full price though.Basically a stunning, beautiful, aesthetically pleasing SHALLOW game.Menu is barebones Unity (and doesn't even save your video or control settings between plays), dying is abrupt, there is no volume or other toggle in the game, etc.To be honest the music is alright for synthwave, but because it slows down when you take damage or lose speed, I found myself turning the entire game sound off in Windows, and just listening to better, higher quality synthwave music off Youtube.Controls are adequate. Sometimes a bit janky, although landing the perfect drift feels nice. Physics likewise get the job done, with little else, especially noticeable in the tedious ""enemy helicopter"" scenes every 8 minutes (which can blow up the road and scatter random debris).All in all feels like a first game project by a dev. A few bugfixes, the ability to import custom music, and a bit more meat on the game side, wheel support (Logitech G27 would be a hoot), customization of car/track/girl/enemies/etc. and MOST importantly endless procedurally generated tracks/roads (instead of the same loop you complete in ~10 minutes and do endlessly after).But considering the dev has basically abandoned this game I don't think any of that will happen. And so OutDrive falls short of it's amazing visuals and potential, which is really quite a sad waste."
